George Thomas MORTON v. S. A. DORSETT. No. 7724. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. May 13, 1937. Lyle Burrow and J. D. Baumgardner, both of Bristol, Tenn., for appellant. T. R. Bandy, of Kingsport, Tenn.,. for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of appellee, accompanied tby certificate of the clerk of the District ■•Court as required by rule 18, it is ordered that the appeal herein be, and the same is, docketed and dismissed.
